          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "5",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "After exploring almost all schools in the PCMC area we decided on SVIS for our daughter. I am quite satisfied with the teachers and the management team. They keep parents up to date on every information parents may want to know about their children. people say that the principle is strict, yes she is strict, and she has to be like that in order to keep the school running in the disciplined manner. I have seen parents creating all the nuisance despite giving clear instructions on everything, so I am not really surprised if teachers and principle are strict towards parents. But they treat all students with atmost care and love. The best thing l liked about the school is - teachers don't give those useless projects to students which they can't do by themselves and end up eating parents brain for completing the project. As parent, I only work on my office project :P",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "SADHU VASWANI INTERNATIONAL SCHOOL - MOSHI"
          },
