            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Ashish"
          },
          "datePublished": "2022-11-16",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "5",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "My 4 years old child is in the Nursery class of SVIS. I am thoroughly satisfied with the school. My two nephews 12 and 7 are also studying in the same school. The school has qualified, compassionate and proactive teachers. The school has many facilities including an excellent swimming pool to encourage kids for extra curricular activities.\n\nThe best thing I found about the school is that they teach Sanskrit shlokas and celebrate all the major Hindu festivals along with the kids. Something that is missing from many English medium schools. Though the school fees is in premium range, I think it is worth it all things considered.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
